    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the species Populus deltoides, native to the lower Mississippi Valley. It has a soft, pale color, fine grain, uniform texture, works easily, and stains well; however, the wood has a tendency to warp. It is used for millwork, musical instruments, paneling, packing boxes, paper pulp, and excelsior.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
